TXDPS Architecture Review Board (ARB) Submission Form
Microsoft Forms Import Template

Instructions:
1. Copy this content into Microsoft Forms
2. Each section below represents a question
3. Use the question type indicators to set up proper form fields

=== BEGIN FORM QUESTIONS ===

Question 1: Submitter Name
Type: Text (Short answer)
Required: Yes

Question 2: Submitter Email
Type: Text (Short answer)
Required: Yes
Validation: Email format

Question 3: Project Name
Type: Text (Short answer)
Required: Yes

Question 4: Project Description
Type: Text (Long answer)
Required: Yes

Question 5: Project Type
Type: Choice (Dropdown)
Required: Yes
Options:
- New Application
- Enhancement
- Integration
- Infrastructure
- Security

Question 6: Application Platform
Type: Choice (Dropdown)
Required: No
Options:
- Web Application
- Mobile Application
- Desktop Application
- Cloud Service
Branching: Show only if Project Type = "New Application"

Question 7: Security Requirements
Type: Text (Long answer)
Required: No
Branching: Show only if Project Type = "Security"

Question 8: Estimated Number of Users
Type: Text (Short answer)
Required: Yes

Question 9: Budget Range
Type: Choice (Dropdown)
Required: Yes
Options:
- Under $50,000
- $50,000 - $100,000
- $100,000 - $500,000
- $500,000 - $1,000,000
- Over $1,000,000

Question 10: Target Completion Date
Type: Date
Required: Yes

Question 11: Business Justification
Type: Text (Long answer)
Required: Yes

Question 12: Risk Assessment
Type: Text (Long answer)
Required: No

Question 13: Dependencies
Type: Text (Long answer)
Required: No

Question 14: Compliance Requirements
Type: Text (Long answer)
Required: No

Question 15: Additional Comments
Type: Text (Long answer)
Required: No

=== END FORM QUESTIONS ===

Additional Settings:
- Enable response receipts
- Collect respondent names
- Allow one response per person
- Show progress bar
- Customize theme with TXDPS colors

Integration:
After creating the form, set up Power Automate to:
1. Capture form responses
2. Write to SharePoint list "ARB Submissions"
3. Send email notifications to ARB team
4. Trigger approval workflow
